<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Sudoku Backend API</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #f8f9fa;
    }
    h1 {
      color: #1a0dab;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #dee2e6;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
    }
    h2 {
      margin-top: 30px;
      color: #006621;
    }
    pre, code {
      background-color: #e9ecef;
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-family: SFMono-Regular, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", Menlo, monospace;
      font-size: 0.9em;
    }
    pre {
      padding: 15px;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
    .endpoint {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
      border-radius: 6px;
      background-color: #fff;
      padding: 15px;
    }
    .method {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 4px 8px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 0.85em;
      color: #fff;
      margin-right: 10px;
    }
    .method-get { background-color: #28a745; }
    .method-post { background-color: #007bff; }
    .footer {
      margin-top: 50px;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 0.85em;
      color: #6c757d;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Sudoku Web Game - API Boilerplate</h1>
  <p>Welcome to the Sinatra + SQLite3 Sudoku Backend API. You can use the following contracts to build your frontend interface.</p>

  <h2>API Endpoints</h2>

  <!-- GET /api/puzzle -->
  <div class="endpoint">
    <p>
      <span class="method method-get">GET</span>
      <code>/api/puzzle?difficulty=easy|medium|hard</code>
    </p>
    <p>Generates a new valid Sudoku puzzle and caches the full solution in the session.</p>
    <p><strong>Response format (JSON):</strong></p>
    <pre>{
  "puzzle": [
    [0, 5, 0, 0, 7, 0, 0, 0, 1],
    ...
  ],
  "difficulty": "medium"
}</pre>
  </div>

  <!-- GET /api/leaderboard -->
  <div class="endpoint">
    <p>
      <span class="method method-get">GET</span>
      <code>/api/leaderboard?difficulty=easy|medium|hard</code>
    </p>
    <p>Fetches the top 10 fastest times for the requested difficulty level.</p>
    <p><strong>Response format (JSON):</strong></p>
    <pre>[
  {
    "username": "alice",
    "time_spent_seconds": 120,
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "created_at": "2026-06-17 12:00:00"
  }
]</pre>
  </div>

  <!-- POST /api/leaderboard -->
  <div class="endpoint">
    <p>
      <span class="method method-post">POST</span>
      <code>/api/leaderboard</code>
    </p>
    <p>Saves a new completion time to the leaderboard.</p>
    <p><strong>Request format (JSON):</strong></p>
    <pre>{
  "username": "bob",
  "time": 245,
  "difficulty": "medium"
}</pre>
    <p><strong>Response format (JSON):</strong></p>
    <pre>{
  "message": "Score saved successfully."
}</pre>
  </div>

  <div class="footer">
    Powered by Ruby, Sinatra, and SQLite3.
  </div>
</body>
</html>
